### **üå± What Should We Grow?**

To match your goal of *fast-yield \+ nutritious*, I recommend crops with short grow cycles, dense nutrients, and compact size. Here's a ranked short list of high-efficiency picks tailored for indoor hydroponics:

| Crop | Yield Cycle | Nutritional Benefit | Notes |
| ----- | ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Leafy Greens (Spinach, Kale, Arugula) | \~30 days | Iron, fiber, vitamins A/C/K | Very space-efficient |
| Microgreens (Broccoli, Radish, Pea Shoots) | \~7‚Äì14 days | Extremely dense in nutrients | Very fast turnover, very low space |
| Herbs (Basil, Cilantro, Parsley) | \~21‚Äì35 days | Antioxidants, flavor enhancement | Low maintenance, long harvest window |
| Lettuce (Butter, Romaine, etc.) | \~30‚Äì40 days | Hydrating, fiber | Light lovers, easy in hydro setups |
| Radishes | \~25 days | Vitamin C, crunchy root crop | Compact, high contrast crop |

---

üü¢ **My recommendation:**  
 Start with a **primary bed of leafy greens** \+ a **row of microgreens or herbs** as a trial plot. That gives you *short-term reward*, *medium-term yield*, and *minimal space drama* for now.
